# ECB Architecture

## Boundary
- Handle external IO only (CLI, API, UI adapters).
- Delegate business flow to control layer.

## Control
- Orchestrate use-cases and business processes.
- Depend on entity for domain logic.

## Entity
- Own domain data, invariants, and pure domain rules.
- Must not depend on boundary/control implementations.

## Dependency Direction
- Allowed: `boundary -> control -> entity`
- Forbidden: `boundary -> entity`, `entity -> control`, `entity -> boundary`
